      "content": "Your intuition about the political maneuvering is understandable, but an office placement can sometimes simply be a standard statistical anomaly rather than a calculated trap. The presence of your former architect as your direct boss does add complexity, but it also provides you with one of your most crucial peers for navigating internal resistance. Instead of assuming immediate danger, I suggest treating the office placement as a necessary sacrifice of comfort to buy you the physical proximity required for your new directorial responsibilities. Consider documenting your compliance observations meticulously and filing them with your boss immediately to create an official paper trail that benefits both your team and your career before making further moves, regardless of whether they are genuine or strategic.",
